## Slide Templates

### Title Slide
```html
<div class="slide title-slide">
  <h1>Presentation Title</h1>
  <h2>Subtitle or Tagline</h2>
  <div class="presenter-info">
    <p>Presenter Name</p>
    <p>Position, Company</p>
    <p>Date</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Content Slide
```html
<div class="slide content-slide">
  <h2>Section Title</h2>
  <div class="content-columns">
    <div class="text-column">
      <ul>
        <li>Key point one with supporting detail</li>
        <li>Key point two with supporting detail</li>
        <li>Key point three with supporting detail</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="visual-column">
      <!-- Visual element: image, chart, diagram -->
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Data Visualization Slide
```html
<div class="slide data-slide">
  <h2>Data Insights</h2>
  <div class="chart-container">
    <!-- Chart or data visualization -->
  </div>
  <div class="insights">
    <p class="insight-highlight">Key insight from the data</p>
    <p class="insight-detail">Brief explanation of significance</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Presentation Style Guide

1. **Typography**
   - Headings: Open Sans Bold, 36-48pt
   - Body: Open Sans Regular, 24-30pt
   - Accent text: Open Sans Semibold Italic, 24-30pt

2. **Color Palette**
   - Primary: #0047AB (Brand blue)
   - Secondary: #F8F8F8 (Light gray)
   - Accent: #FF6B35 (Orange)
   - Text: #333333 (Dark gray)
   - Background: #FFFFFF (White)

3. **Visual Elements**
   - Use icons from a consistent set
   - Photos should be high-resolution and professionally sourced
   - Charts should use the core color palette
   - Apply subtle shadows for depth when appropriate